  </div><div
      class="comment-text markdown-body "
      id="ct-1" data-comment-id="14453035" data-ismarkdown="true" ><p>The link below shows the information that has been verified for this root inclusion request. Search in the page for the word &quot;NEED&quot; to see where further clarification is requested. Please add a comment to this bug when you have provided all of the requested information.</p>
<p><a href="https://ccadb-public.secure.force.com/mozilla/PrintViewForCase?CaseNumber=00000396" rel="nofollow">https://ccadb-public.secure.force.com/mozilla/PrintViewForCase?CaseNumber=00000396</a></p>
<p>In particular, please provide the following:</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Version table or changelog in the CPS.<br>
<a href="https://wiki.mozilla.org/CA/Required_or_Recommended_Practices#CP.2FCPS_Revision_Table" rel="nofollow">https://wiki.mozilla.org/CA/Required_or_Recommended_Practices#CP.2FCPS_Revision_Table</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Check usage of &quot;No stipulation&quot; throughout CPS.<br>
<a href="https://wiki.mozilla.org/CA/Required_or_Recommended_Practices#CP.2FCPS_Structured_According_to_RFC_3647" rel="nofollow">https://wiki.mozilla.org/CA/Required_or_Recommended_Practices#CP.2FCPS_Structured_According_to_RFC_3647</a><br>
The words &quot;No Stipulation&quot; mean that the particular document imposes no requirements related to that section.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>CPS section that describes how the CA must verify the email address to be included in the certificate.<br>
<a href="https://wiki.mozilla.org/CA/Required_or_Recommended_Practices#Verifying_Email_Address_Control" rel="nofollow">https://wiki.mozilla.org/CA/Required_or_Recommended_Practices#Verifying_Email_Address_Control</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>A public URL through which the CA certificate can be directly downloaded.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Add records for the existing intermediate certs to the CCADB as described here: <a href="https://ccadb.org/cas/intermediates#adding-intermediate-certificate-data" rel="nofollow">https://ccadb.org/cas/intermediates#adding-intermediate-certificate-data</a></p>
</li>
</ol>
